Class CCAssignableMethodsBaseImpl<E extends CCAssignable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.assignment.CCAssignableMethodsBaseImpl<E>

    CCAssignableMethods

    public abstract class CCAssignableMethodsBaseImpl<E extends CCAssignable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements CCAssignableMethods
    Abstract superclass for all implementors of CCAssignableMethods. Hides the complexity of some of the public methods and calls out to abstract template methods to fill in the details.

    • Method Detail

      • createAssignmentReviewActivity

        public Activity createAssignmentReviewActivity()
        Create a new assignment review activity which represents the responsibility to assign this assignable. Assignment review activities are used for manual assignment.

        The default implementation of this method creates an assignment review activity and populates it using the AssignmentReviewActivitySubject and AssignmentReviewActivityLinkProperty properties. This implementation should be sufficient for most new assignable types.

        Specified by:
        createAssignmentReviewActivity in interface CCAssignableMethods
        Returns:
        a new assignment review activity which refers to this assignable

      • findAssignmentReviewActivities

        public IQueryResult<Activity,Activity> findAssignmentReviewActivities()
        Find any existing open assignment review activities related to this assignable. Normally this will return either zero or one activities. Assignment review activities are used for manual assignment.

        The default implementation of this method looks for open assignment review activities where the AssignmentReviewActivityLinkProperty of this object is equal to this. For example if this object is an exposure it looks for open assignment review activities where Activity.Exposure is equal to this exposure. This implementation should be sufficient for most new assignable types (though it is not suitable for Claim, which needs to check that only the Claim foreign key is set)

        Specified by:
        findAssignmentReviewActivities in interface CCAssignableMethods
        Returns:
        a query result containing the open assignment review activities, if any

      • createAssignmentHistoryEvent

        public History createAssignmentHistoryEvent(Assignable assignable)
        The default implementation of this method just creates a history event directly on the claim, with no other foreign keys set. Subclassers which want to create a history event with a foreign key set (such as Exposure, Matter), should override this method, call super.createAssignmentHistoryEvent(), and then set the foreign key. Subclassers which want to avoid creating a history event (such as Activity) should override this method to return null

        One extra subtlety; this method keeps track of the history event it creates. If the method is called again and the event it created last time is still in the bundle and is still uncommitted then it will delete the old event before creating the new one.

        Specified by:
        createAssignmentHistoryEvent in interface CCAssignableMethods
        Parameters:
        assignable - the assignable containing details of the new assignment
        Returns:
        the new history event, or null

      • shouldCascadeAssignment

        public boolean shouldCascadeAssignment(Assignable parent,
                                       Key defaultOwnerUserId,
                                       Key defaultGroupId)
        Called on an assignable to decide if the assignment on the parent assignable should be cascaded to this assignable. The default implementation checks the following:
        • If this assignable is in pending assignment state then always cascade
        • If this assignable is assigned to the default user and group then always cascade
        • if the target's new group is undefined or it is the same as the parent's previous group (basically a group check, ensure that the assignment stays within the group) and the target's assignment status is not MANUAL and one of the following is true:
          • the target has no assigned user and no assigned queue or
          • the target's assigned user is the same as the parent's previously assigned user or
          • target's assigned queue is the same as the parent's previously assigned queue
        Subclassers can override this method to impose additional conditions. For example matter might override this method, call super, and then add an additional check that only allows cascading if the matter is open.
        Specified by:
        shouldCascadeAssignment in interface CCAssignableMethods
        Parameters:
        parent - the parent assignable
        defaultOwnerUserId - the id of the special default owner user, used by the assignment engine as the user of last resort if, for example, assignment rules can't find an appropriate user.
        defaultGroupId - the id of the root group, used by the assignment engine as the group of last resort if, for example, assignment rules can't find an appropriate group.
        Returns:
        true if the assignment should be cascaded, false otherwise

      • getOwningAssignable

        public Assignable getOwningAssignable()
        Called by the "assignToClaimOwner" method to determine which assignable "owns" the current assignable so the owners assignment information can be copied. The owner is nearly always just the claim though there is a special case - if an activity belongs to an exposure then the exposure is the owner. If this method return null the assignToClaimOwner call will return false.

        The default implementation just returns the claim, as returned by the Claim property

        Specified by:
        getOwningAssignable in interface CCAssignableMethods
        Returns:
        the owning assignable, usually the claim

      • getAssignmentReviewActivitySubject

        public abstract java.lang.String getAssignmentReviewActivitySubject()
        The value to put in the subject field of an assignment review activity for this assignable. If this property returns null then this assignable cannot be manually assigned.
        Returns:
        an assignment review subject string

      • getAssignmentReviewActivityLinkProperty

        public abstract ILinkPropertyInfo getAssignmentReviewActivityLinkProperty()
        The property on activity that is set for an assignment review activity. An assignment review activity represents the responsibility to assign another assignable object. This link property points to the other assignable object that needs to be assigned. So, for example, if the current object is a Claim this property will return the Activity.Claim property. If it is an activity, it will return the Activity.RelatedActivity property.
        Returns:
        the property on an assignment review activity that points to the current type of assignable
